@ezyang Yes, the map was always empty when calling CUDAHooksRegistry().
Loading the dylib works as expected that it is reusing the same static Registry and registers the key. However calling CUDAHooksRegistry() doesn't get the same static Registry instance, instead it creates a new one.
Could it be relating to how mac handles dynamic loading? e.g different memory space?

